/** * Retrieve the first item from the first map, assuming that there is just * one item and just one map, and that the item is a number. * This is the typical case: a single, numeric generated key. *

Keys are held in a List of Maps, where each item in the list represents * the keys for each row. If there are multiple columns, then the Map will have * multiple entries as well. If this method encounters multiple entries in * either the map or the list meaning that multiple keys were returned, * then an InvalidDataAccessApiUsageException is thrown. * @return the generated key as a number * @throws InvalidDataAccessApiUsageException if multiple keys are encountered */
